<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1167793776600">
<term>Green’s theorem</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167793776606">relates the integral over a connected region to an integral over the boundary of the region</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167793776611">
<term>stream function</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167793776616">if <m:math><m:mrow><m:mstyle mathvariant="bold" mathsize="normal"><m:mtext>F</m:mtext></m:mstyle><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo>〈</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mi>P</m:mi><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mi>Q</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mo>〉</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> is a source-free vector field, then stream function <emphasis effect="italics">g</emphasis> is a function such that <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>P</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:msub><m:mi>g</m:mi><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:msub></m:mrow></m:math> and <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>Q</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mtext>−</m:mtext><m:msub><m:mi>g</m:mi><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:msub></m:mrow></m:math></meaning>
</definition>
